reviewText:
I'm not a big fan of FPS games, and the Call of Duty series especially annoys me. However I'm loving this game, despite it sharing a lot of similarities with Call of Duty, including two out of three words of the title. How's that so? Well, two reasons, mainly:

1) the gameplay is made slightly more arcade-y than the CoD I remember playing by the presence of scores and combo multipliers. It's not the trick glory that was Bulletstorm but it's still pretty good to turn the experience into a neat game of skill;

2) the story and the voice acting are straight up awesome and set up a wonderful mood, while being tongue-in-cheek and not taking themselves too seriously. The best bit is that the whole plot is basically a collection of tall tales told by an old bounty hunter at a saloon, so he's all but reliable. And this reflects on the gameplay as objects pop out of air as he remembers them (or makes them up?) and entire sections of the story are rewritten on the fly (but still leave you the experience and skills acquired). This is quite original and it helps keeping the narration fun and not merely a bland pretext for killing more bandits.

